trend_summary: Earliest to latest scenes show progressive suburban infill: vacant patches convert to housing, industrial/commercial blocks enlarge near the central corridor, and new interchanges widen the main east-west highway. Tree cover stays extensive, aided by riparian and roadside greening. Overall built footprint climbs steadily, giving the landscape clear medium-density, predominantly suburban character.
notable_changes: Gradual conversion of open lots in north and center into residential neighborhoods.
Expansion of light-industrial/commercial complexes around the mid-eastern sector.
Upgrading and lane additions along the primary east-west highway and associated interchanges.
Increase in roadside and riverside vegetation buffers despite higher construction activity.
Redevelopment of several large-roof facilities, replacing older structures with denser mixed-use buildings.
